main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed over Rabat, French Morocco on September 6, 1952.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 10-15 minutes and the object was described as circular, approximately 20-25 meters in diameter emitting a bright light., The object was estimated to be traveling at a high speed of about 600 to 800 miles per hour at an altitude of 30,000 to 40,000 feet., Multiple reports were filed by French civil air control personnel and military personnel at the airfield regarding the sighting., The weather conditions during the sighting were reported as clear with visible stars., It was reported that the object maneuvered silently and left no exhaust trail.
sighted object: round unidentified aerial object emitting bright light
witness description: French civil air control personnel and military personnel at Rabat, French Morocco airfield
